added.title: Mr. Butt
added.description: After Starfire is set up by Blackfire and sent to prison, the Titans work to make Blackfire a better sister while Starfire plots her revenge.

added.title: Man Person
added.description: Despite the Titans' protests, Beast Boy becomes convinced that replacing his body parts with robotic limbs makes him more manly.

added.title: Pirates
added.description: When Aqualad and Raven fall for each other, Beast Boy fights this match - with intensity.

added.title: Money Grandma
added.description: When Robin starts a smear campaign against the other Titans so that he can be reelected Team Leader, Raven brings in a great leader from the past to teach Robin a thing or two.

added.title: Brian
added.description: When The Brain captures the Titans to fuel Project B.R.I.A.N., the Titan's little buddies are the only heroes who can save them.

added.title: Salty Codgers
added.description: Raven is delighted when the other Titans are magically turned into old people during a battle.

added.title: Friendship
added.description: Zapped into an episode of Pretty Pretty Pegasus, the Titans must fight their way out using love and friendship.

added.title: The Mask
added.description: Robin's mask doesn't just conceal his secret identity, it hides a terrible secret!

added.title: Serious Business
added.description: The Titans learn the hard way what a bathroom is really for.

added.title: I See You
added.description: Robin brings Starfire on a fake stakeout in an attempt to get a kiss, while Cyborg and Beast Boy hold their own stakeout to discover Raven's dark secret.

added.title: Nature
added.description: In order to get his powers back, Beast Boy returns to nature and finds it much harsher than he expects.

added.title: Knowledge
added.description: Starfire wants to learn more, but will knowledge make her a bummer?

added.title: Sandwich Thief
added.description: Robin's perfect sandwich is missing and he will stop at nothing to find it.

added.title: Vegetables
added.description: The Titans try vegetarianism, but learn that not everyone is cut out for that lifestyle.

added.title: Slumber Party
added.description: The Titans throw a slumber party to help Cyborg get over his fear of Scary Teri.

added.title: The Colossus
added.description: Gumball and Darwin learn that it isn't wise to upset Hector, Elmore's resident Giant.

added.title: The Knights
added.description: Gumball and Tobias compete for Penny's affection by putting on the lamest duel in history.

added.title: The Fridge
added.description: When Mom discovers Gumball has no ambition she is determined to turn him into a winner.

added.title: The Flower
added.description: When Gumball sees Leslie with Penny, he is overcome with uncontrollable jealousy.

added.title: The Banana
added.description: Darwin lends his pen to Banana Joe but, when it comes back chewed, Gumball's thoughts turn to revenge.

added.title: The Job
added.description: Dad gets his first job as a pizza delivery guy, which rocks the very fabric of the universe.

added.title: The Remote
added.description: The Wattersons' battle for possession of the TV remote gets dirty.

added.title: The Treasure
added.description: Anais uncovers a secret that she's convinced will lead her to the Watterson's hidden family treasure.

added.title: The Apology
added.description: For once in his life Gumball is the one who's owed an apology...from Ms Simian!

added.title: The Words
added.description: Darwin is too polite to speak his mind, so Gumball teaches him to be direct via an epic battle of insults.

added.title: The Skull
added.description: Gumball and Darwin make friends with classmate Clayton, a compulsive liar who can shape-change!

added.title: The Bet
added.description: When Bobert becomes Gumball's servant for a week, Gumball realizes robots obey everyone's command... even if that means destroying you!

added.title: The Watch
added.description: Gumball and Darwin learn that getting a family heirloom back off an old man is harder than you might think.

added.title: The Phone
added.description: When Gumball and Darwin get their first cell phone, they foolishly give out their number to super-intense Ocho.

added.title: Memories of Bobby
added.description: When a pillar of the Creek community leaves, our trio mourns their loss by remembering the good times.

added.title: Jacob of the Creek
added.description: A terrible haircut forces Craig to go undercover at the Creek.

added.title: Return of the Honeysuckle Rangers
added.description: Craig discovers that the Honeysuckle Rangers have snuck into his side of the Creek to steal his most prized possession.

added.title: Kelsey the Elder
added.description: A spat between the Elders of the Creek leaves an opening in their tabletop role playing game, so Kelsey joins the campaign!

added.title: Sour Candy Trials
added.description: Craig goes on a mind-bending journey as he tries to eat the most sour candy in the Creek!

added.title: Fort Williams
added.description: When Craig can't go to the Creek, he and his mom decide to build the biggest blanket fort in the world!

added.title: Summer Wish
added.description: When Craig decides to keep a lightning bug in a jar, he disrupts the delicate balance of Summer.

added.title: Turning the Tables
added.description: Craig dines at the restaurant where his older brother works and orders up a plate of REVENGE... and lots of breadsticks.

added.title: Kelsey the Author
added.description: Craig and Stacks help Kelsey become a real author turning her story into a book!

added.title: Council of the Creek
added.description: The circle game wreaks havoc on the Creek, so Craig forms a council to restore order.

added.title: Sparkle Cadet
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP team up with an intergalactic hero named Sparkle Cadet, hoping to save the Creek from negativity.

added.title: Cousin of the Creek
added.description: Craig takes his cousin, Bryson, to the Creek, and accidentally starts a water balloon war.

added.title: Camper on the Run
added.description: A runaway from a summer camp ends up at the Stump, but Craig suspects her story may not be what it seems.

added.title: Stink Bomb
added.description: An accidental stink bomb explosion causes the kids to evacuate the Creek, but Craig takes it upon himself to rescue those left behind in the stench.

added.title: Falafel's Passion
added.description: Apple and Onion try to help Falafel find his passion but it looks like things might take a humiliating turn.

added.title: Hole In Roof
added.description: Suddenly the hole in the roof is no longer a laughing matter but one of a life or death.

added.title: Patty's Law
added.description: If found guilty of breaking Patty's Law, Apple and Onion face grave punishment but they have a more pressing concern; looking after their dear, sickly Falafel.

added.title: The Eater
added.description: It's Halloween and Apple's not feeling quite right. He takes Onion into the dark depths to find out why.

added.title: Apple & Onion's Booth
added.description: Apple and Onion must save their favorite booth at Pizza's Diner from a Texas oil tycoon.

added.title: Ferekh
added.description: Apple and Onion are put in charge of Falafel's beloved rooster but it turns out that other parties have a vested interest in it too.

added.title: Pat on the Head
added.description: Apple and Onion are to cook for a very important guest but Onion is not quite feeling himself.

added.title: Falafel's Glory
added.description: Apple and Onion must recruit the help of retired quiz master Falafel if they are to not starve.

added.title: Christmas Spirit
added.description: Apple & Onion know exactly what gifts they want this Christmas but all their money has been squandered. Luckily they find a suitably festive way to make back that money.

added.title: Slobbery
added.description: Burger's roommate is not only a problem for him, but for Apple and Onion who need Burger's help for something else.

added.title: Microwave's Dance Club
added.description: DJ Saltfish and MC Ackee are in town for two nights only and Apple and Onion are determined to make the most of it and bust some moves on the dance floor.

added.title: All Work and No Play
added.description: Having finally saved up and aquired an expensive toy race track, Apple and Onion are faced with one problem- there is no time to play with it.

added.title: Drone Shoes
added.description: Can there exist such a thing as drone shoes? It sounds like they would need a huge power capacity.

added.title: Walking on the Ceiling
added.description: Apple's curiosity of what it would be like to walk upside down like a spider should be ignored and given no further thought. It is not.

added.title: Keep It Fresh
added.description: It's Apple's turn to buy this months' groceries again meaning that the risk of starvation is at hand.

added.title: Viral Video
added.description: The Bears think they have what it takes to make and star in a viral video, but when Nom-Nom decides that they don't, Grizz breaks into the koala's limo in an effort to change his mind.

added.title: Food Truck
added.description: The Bears open up a food truck after being disappointed by the food options available to them. In an effort to drum up business, they start selling their food to animals until the animals go a little crazy.

added.title: Chloe
added.description: Chloe spends time with the Bears in an effort to research them for an upcoming presentation. But when the Bears sneak a peek at her very dry report, the Bears decide to jazz it up with exaggerated facts about themselves and their lifestyle.

added.title: Panda's Date
added.description: When a vendor at the Farmer's Market (LUCY) sticks Panda with an EpiPen reviving him after an allergic reaction, Panda comes to in the arms of his dream girl. Panda tries to woo this woman of his dreams but his brothers and his own insecurities get in the way.

added.title: Everyday Bears
added.description: It's a normal day for the Bears. This means that Ice gets in a fight with a Roomba, Panda's life gets turned upside down when a mouse invades his room and Grizz gets stuck in a tree. You know, everyday stuff for a bear.

added.title: Primal
added.description: Have the Bears lost their survival instincts by living in the modern world? Grizz wants to know so he purposefully gets the Bears lost in the deep forest.

added.title: Jean Jacket
added.description: The Bears find a bedazzled jean jacket in a dumpster. It's just about the coolest thing they've ever seen and seems to make the wearer of the jacket extremely lucky. But after the Bears fight over who gets control of the jacket, they have to consider that their denim blessing has become a curse.

added.title: Nom Nom
added.description: When Nom Nom shows up on the Bears' doorstep, disheveled and deposed from his spot as cutest internet star ever after a recent meltdown, he enlists the Bears to help him regain his title.

added.title: Shush Ninjas
added.description: The Bears are fed up with the decay of etiquette at today's theaters. The Bears take it upon themselves to be the police of the theater, sneaking up like ninjas to shush people who ruin the movie for others with their bad manners.

added.title: My Clique
added.description: Chloe, a child prodigy, finds it difficult to connect with her much older classmates. The Bears take her under their wing and show her how to make great college friends.

added.title: Charlie
added.description: You know that one annoying friend who just can't get the hint? That's Charlie, and he's Bigfoot. The Bears meet him when Charlie signs up on a home-sharing website to spend a weekend with the Bears. Charlie is the worst possible house guest for the Bears and nearly destroys their house.

added.title: Brother Up
added.description: After Panda stumbles and accidentally scares a pack of wolves away in the process, the hierarchy of the Bears is disrupted. Suddenly, Panda has become the alpha bear, and he and Grizz have to deal with the consequences of an emotional Panda being the leader of the three Bears.

added.title: Occupy Bears
added.description: When the city plans to destroy the Bears' cave in order to make way for a new cell phone tower, Grizz and Panda must find evidence from their past that proves they have rights to their land. And in case that fails, Ice Bear protests and tries to sabotage the construction crew.

added.title: The Kindergarten Kid
added.description: Steven and the Gems deal with a monster problem.

added.title: Know Your Fusion
added.description: Steven and the Gems delve deep into what makes a fusion so special.

added.title: Buddy's Book
added.description: Steven and Connie take a trip to the library and discover a long forgotten book.

added.title: Mindful Education
added.description: Steven and Connie need to learn greater focus to take their training to the next level.

added.title: Future Boy Zoltron
added.description: Steven fills in for a fortune teller at Funland.

added.title: Last One Out of Beach City
added.description: Pearl, Steven and Amethyst go to a rock show.

added.title: Onion Gang
added.description: Steven learns about Onion's secret group of friends.

added.title: Three Gems and a Baby
added.description: Greg tells Steven the story of his first winter with Steven.

added.title: Steven's Dream
added.description: A strange dream prompts Steven to search for answers.

added.title: Adventures in Light Distortion
added.description: Steven and the Gems take off on a search and recovery mission.

added.title: Gem Heist
added.description: The Gems try to pull of a heist.

added.title: The Zoo
added.description: Steven visits a special zoo.

added.title: That Will Be All
added.description: Steven and the Gems make a daring escape!

added.title: The New Crystal Gems
added.description: Connie helps look after Beach City while Steven is busy.

added.title: Fragments
added.description: Steven heads to the woods to train with a powerful mentor.

added.title: Homeworld Bound
added.description: Steven heads to the Diamonds for advice on how to control his new powers.

added.title: Everything's Fine
added.description: Steven insists that everything is fine.

added.title: I Am My Monster
added.description: Everything is not fine.

added.title: The Future
added.description: Steven is finally ready to move on.

added.title: Storytelling
added.description: When Jake becomes sick, the only thing that can cure him is a good story, so he asks Finn to go out and find one. The story must have excitement, romance, suspense and, of course, a happy ending. When nothing interesting happens, Finn tries to make the story happen, accidentally turning the forest animals against each other and him!

added.title: Slow Love
added.description: A lonely snail lookin' for love literally crashes into the treehouse and asks Finn and Jake for help. Now, our heroes must teach this snail how to get a girlfriend before he destroys their home!

added.title: Power Animal
added.description: Finn is kidnapped by a group of gnomes, who want to harness his energy to take over the world. Only Jake can save his best friend if he can just focus long enough to follow the obvious clues and rescue Finn.

added.title: The Other Tarts
added.description: Finn and Jake volunteer for a dangerous assignment: currying rare tarts for a meeting of Ooo royalty.

added.title: To Cut a Woman's Hair
added.description: Finn needs to find a princess willing to give up a lock of her hair to save Jake from a balding witch.

added.title: The Pods
added.description: Finn and Jake must sort out the good magic beans from the bad.

added.title: Her Parents
added.description: Jake pretends to be a rainicorn in order to make Lady's parents like him.

added.title: The Real You
added.description: Finn has to give a speech at Princess Bubblegum's science barbecue and seeks out a quick fix to make himself smarter.

added.title: Crystals Have Power
added.description: Jake takes a vow of non-violence, which is inconvenient when they're attacked by marauders from the crystal dimension.

added.title: The Chamber of Frozen Blades
added.description: In Ninja-mode, Finn and Jake break into Ice King's palace to catch him red-handed.

added.title: The Silent King
added.description: Finn and Jake get to live like royalty, but soon fine the easy life doesn't suit them. Or at least not Finn.

added.title: Laundry Woes
added.description: Mordecai wants to return Margaret's sweater to her.

added.title: Silver Dude
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to make money for a video game by street performing.

added.title: Benson's Car
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to fix Benson's car before he finds out they broke its window.

added.title: Every Meat Burritos
added.description: Mordecai, Rigby, Muscle Man and Fives want Every Meat Burritos from the Jimbros' Burritos drive-thru.

added.title: Wall Buddy
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to clean up their room.

added.title: A Skips in Time
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to help Skips return Teenage Skips to the 1700s.

added.title: Survival Skills
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to bring Benson some tortillas.

added.title: The Previous Owner
added.description: Each of the park guys want to win a bet by telling the scariest story at a Halloween party.

added.title: Tants
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to get back a gift that Pops gave them.

added.title: Bank Shot
added.description: Rigby has to win a bet by beating a guy at basketball bank shots.

added.title: Power Tower
added.description: Muscle Man wants to win the bodybuilding competition at his gym.

added.title: The Heart of a Stuntman
added.description: Muscle Man, Rigby, Mordecai and High Fives want to get a stuntman license for Timmy's birthday party.

added.title: Dodge This
added.description: The park guys want to win a dodge ball tournament.

added.title: Portable Toilet
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to get out of a portable toilet.

added.title: The Postcard
added.description: High Five Ghost wants to reunite with a girl from his past.

added.title: Stray Bullet
added.description: In order to save an innocent squirrel, Bubbles gives him a dash of Chemical X, giving him some super squirrel powers.

added.title: All Chalked Up
added.description: Him tricks Bubbles into bringing her chalk drawings to life, who then proceed to wreak havoc in Townsville.

added.title: Knock It Off
added.description: When the Professor's college roommate sees his old pal's brilliant creations, he decides to cash in on the popularity of the Powerpuffs.

added.title: Members Only
added.description: When the girls try to join an all-male superhero organization, they learn that sometimes supermen aren't so super.

added.title: Him Diddle Riddle
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls must solve a series of Him's riddles to keep the Professor from having to pay.

added.title: Helter Shelter/Power Lunch
added.description: Helter Shelter: Bubbles has a habit of saving helpless animals and the Professor is sick of it. When Bubbles brings a baby whale home, she and her sisters have a whale of a time hiding this new addition./Power Lunch: The Gangreen Gang shoplifts from a mini-mart, shoveling loads of food down their throats as fast as possible. When the girls fire at them with their laser vision, a strange reaction occurs.

added.title: Forced Kin
added.description: A terrible, evil menace from outer space descends upon Townville. The girls must fight evil with evil so they seek the advice of Mojo Jojo.

added.title: Superfriends
added.description: The new girl next door learns it's hard to be best friends with superheroes and soon starts hanging out with the wrong kind of kid, Princess.

added.title: Not So Secret Service
added.description: After Mojo Jojo's latest creation threatens to blast him into tiny bits, the Powerpuff Girls are forced to take Mojo in.

added.title: Worship
added.description: When the Fashionistas unveil their new mind controlling perfume, the Powerpuff Girls must find a way to stop them before Townsville falls under their spell.

added.title: Blossom3
added.description: After being blasted by Duplikate, Blossom turns into a triple threat.

added.title: Mojo the Great
added.description: In an effort to make himself great, Mojo steals the powers that makes the each of the Powerpuff girls the heroes they are.

added.title: Trouble Clef
added.description: When Morbucks realizes that The Powerpuff Girls see her as a villain and not a friend, she sets out to turn the town against them.

added.title: Save the Date
added.description: Ms. Keane is nervous about a first date.

added.title: Can't Buy Love
added.description: When Morbucks falls in love, she finds the first thing money can't buy.

added.title: Largo
added.description: When a mysterious rain cloud plagues Townsville, Bubbles learns things aren't what they seem.

added.title: Blundercup
added.description: Buttercup is knocked off-kilter by a mysterious force.

added.title: Ragnarock and Roll
added.description: When an ancient prophecy spells doom for Townsville, the girls must race to stop it.

added.title: Total Eclipse of the Kart
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls compete in a race against some of their most vicious villains to win whatever is in the Mayor's mysterious box of mystery.

added.title: The Long Skate Home
added.description: After they get accused of a crime they didn't commit, the Powerpuff girls and the Derbytantes have to find a way to clear their name!

added.title: In the Doghouse
added.description: Buttercup must go it alone to save her family from a kidnapping.

added.title: Salamander
added.description: When the professor is kidnapped, the girls must go to a mysterious island to save him.

added.title: Checkin' Out!
added.description: A trip to the supermarket has bizarre consequences.

added.title: Spoooooky Game
added.description: The gang's weekly board game night has been getting a little too competitive lately, so when Unikitty finds a spooky old board game that's clearly haunted, their desire to win gets turned upside down, but cursed or not, they'll be the first to the finish line!

added.title: No Day Like Snow Day
added.description: When a blizzard hits the town, Master Frown tries to ruin everyone's fun by pretending to be a magical snowman! But when he gets frozen inside, Master Frown must worry less about ruining everyone's good time and instead not turning into a Frown-sicle, while he's forced to experience the joys of the holiday season!

added.title: Action Forest
added.description: Hawkodile is the toughest action hero in the land, until his old rival shows up to take vengeance on him. Defeated and in need of help, Hawkodile must train Unikitty and the others into super muscle­y tough bros. And there's only one place unstoppable warriors are made, the Action Forest.

added.title: Kaiju Kitty
added.description: When a giant monster attacks the Unikingdom, the gang fights back with Dr. Fox's awesome new secret weapon: a massive mega robot! But after the threat is contained, Unikitty doesn't want to stop using the  awesome robot, so she finds excuses for them to use it for everything, no matter how pointless. But what if the greatest threat to the kingdom turns out to be them?

added.title: Fire & Nice
added.description: When Master Frown causes Unikitty to have an angry outburst that gets a little too destructive, she wishes her Rage Kitty side wasn't part of her anymore. Thanks to a new Dr. Fox invention, she gets her wish: Rage Kitty and Nice Unikitty split apart into two! But with Unikitty now unable to get angry, she learns bottling up your anger is never a good thing.

added.title: Rock Friend
added.description: Unikitty discovers Puppycorn's only other friend is a boring old rock. Encouraged to "make more friends," Puppycorn just can't find someone he clicks with, until he takes her advice and decides to literally make a new friend out of the best parts of his friends. This won't go well.

added.title: Kitchen Chaos
added.description: After a workplace injury, Richard is unable to do his servant work. Unikitty and the others take on the task of one simple chore, clean the kitchen. This incredibly boring task taxes our heroes as they find every way possible to not do it. Will they be able to accomplish this goal and bring Richard back?

added.title: Crushing Defeat
added.description: When Hawkodile develops a secret crush on Dr. Fox, he finds himself actually crushing down in size! With Hawkodile too embarrassed to tell her (or anyone) about it, Unikitty and the gang become his love gurus to help him confess his feelings before he shrinks away into nothing!

added.title: Wishing Well
added.description: When Puppycorn uses a wishing well and it doesn't come true, Unikitty is shocked to discover the reason: all the wishes made over the years can't be granted because they're trapped at the bottom of the well (it's a dumb system.) She frees them to bring joy to the town… only to discover that they've gone a little bad after years trapped in a dark hole. Soon, they wish it would end!

added.title: Hide N' Seek
added.description: Unikitty is proud to be the reigning champ of Hide N' Seek Day. But when Unikitty finds everyone in the kingdom except for Richard, she hunts him down at all costs. Will Richard continue to elude the Princess at her favorite game, and if so, how?!

added.title: Stuck Together
added.description: When Master Frown's head is stuck on Unikitty's butt, she vows to help him get his own body back, but first, she has to attend to her nice princess duties! But sharing a body with Master Frown can get pretty complicated, especially when Master Frown has his own agenda.

added.title: Little Prince Puppycorn
added.description: Puppycorn finally realizes he's a prince, so he wants to be in charge of the kingdom for once! Despite their friends' concerns, Unikitty makes Puppycorn ruler but realizes absolute power in the hands of the pup is too much for him to handle and his ideas aren't exactly great. Can they remove him from power while keeping the kingdom from revolting?

added.title: Pet Pet
added.description: Unikitty and the gang bring home a tiny creature they name Pet Pet, but Richard won't let them keep it if they can't prove they are responsible owners. But when Pet Pet runs away, Unikitty must pretend to be Pet Pet until they can find him, or Richard will never let them have Pet Pet (or any pet) ever again! Will Unikitty survive pet training, or finally admit responsibility is a lot harder than she thought?

added.title: Kitty Court
added.description: When Unikitty has a little auto incident with Master Frown, he insists on taking it to court! Frown's thrilled. There's nothing worse than boring old court and he can't wait to subject Unikitty to it! Unikitty is happy to make things right but the trial will be in Unikitty Court, which is so nonsensical and fun. It's Frown's worst nightmare! Will Master Frown succeed in bumming Unikitty out? Or will he be the one punished by their legal antics?

added.title: The Interrogation
added.description: After Mr. Reese discovers his precious car smeared with meatball sauce, he pulls out his officer's cap and enlists Clarence to help his investigation to nab the culprit.

added.title: Lost Playground
added.description: When Aberdale Elementary's beloved playground equipment is replaced with safe, boring alternatives, Clarence and the gang seek out their old playground equipment in the legendary lost playground yard.

added.title: Bird Boy Man
added.description: Sumo discovers an injured roadrunner, names him Hot Sauce, and nurses him back to health. The two become inseparable pals, but Sumo learns that a wild animal can't be contained.

added.title: Freedom Cactus
added.description: Clarence draws a comic for the school paper and it becomes a huge hit with the kids. When angry parents step in and censor the comic's crass humor, Clarence must stand up for his artistic vision.

added.title: Plane Excited
added.description: Clarence is all excited visit his grandma when he learns that Chad has never been on a plane. Clarence makes it his mission to help Chad get through a hectic flight.

added.title: Escape from Beyond the Cosmic
added.description: When Clarence accidentally breaks a local arcade game Jeff has become obsessed with, Clarence puts together his own real-life version of the game at home, encouraging Jeff to act out his fantasy in levels created exclusively by Clarence.

added.title: Ren Faire
added.description: Clarence and his pals venture to the Aberdale Renaissance Faire. Clarence confuses a medieval play for reality, and vows to stop the evil black knight from getting the princess.

added.title: Time Crimes
added.description: When Clarence is convinced he has the power to manipulate time he vows to only use his abilities for good. However, a day at school puts his morals to the test when he's given the ultimate choice to help his friends or pause time in the name of fun.

added.title: Saturday School
added.description: After creating an unapproved mural on a wall at Aberdale Elementary, Clarence, Jeff and Sumo are forced to come to school on a Saturday to clean up as punishment.

added.title: Attack the Block Party
added.description: Clarence, Jeff and Sumo investigate a high school party down the street, which they mistake for an alien invasion.

added.title: Field Trippin'
added.description: After a pit stop bathroom break during a school field trip, Clarence returns to the parking lot and accidentally gets on the wrong school bus - which takes him to a different school!

added.title: Ice Cream Hunt
added.description: Clarence enlists the help of his eccentric neighbor Larry to take the trio out for ice cream and the ride of their lives!

added.title: Company Man
added.description: When Clarence loses the ball during a soccer game, he ends up following it into an office building, where he's mistaken for the boss's kid and given free reign to wander around. Will he climb his way to the top of the corporate ladder or end up on the chopping block?

added.title: Stump Brothers
added.description: After Clarence and Sumo cause a power outage in Sumo's family home, they're sent off in the hot desert with Sumo's older brother to retrieve a generator part. Will they survive the trek or will Sumo's sibling rivalry boil over?

added.title: The Tails of Mardrynia
added.description: After reading a book about a mystical animal society in class, Clarence is inspired to round up local animals and recreate an animal world of his own to cheer up his friend Percy. But will Percy take the game too far?

added.title: Inventor Mentor
added.description: Uncle Grandpa goes to Italy to help a young girl who wants to be a great inventor.

added.title: Jerky Jasper
added.description: Uncle Grandpa goes to great lengths to meet Pizza Steve's imaginary friend.

added.title: Dinosaur Day
added.description: Pizza Steve's jealousy ruins Uncle Grandpa's Dinosaur Day celebration for Mr. Gus.

added.title: RV Olympics
added.description: Pizza Steve and Mr. Gus compete in the RV Olympics.

added.title: Uncle Melvins
added.description: Legendary rock band, the Melvins, team up with Uncle Grandpa to help a young girl who wants to win her school's talent show.

added.title: Uncle Baseball
added.description: A failing little league team on the brink of giving up gets help from Uncle Grandpa and some Major League Baseball players.

added.title: Costume Crisis
added.description: Uncle Grandpa makes improvements to a kid's Halloween costume.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Runs for President
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve run against one another in the RV presidential race.

added.title: Chill Out
added.description: Uncle Grandpa takes a kid to the North Pole for an epic snowball battle.

added.title: The Bike Ride
added.description: Pizza Steve desperately tries to prevent the gang from finding out his shameful secret.

added.title: Mr. Gus Moves Out
